The paper deals with developing intelligent traffic control algorithms for signalized intersections in networked transportation systems, which involves the use of connected-vehicle technology. This falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) as it involves coordination among multiple agents (vehicles) to optimize traffic flow. The paper also deals with networked transportation systems, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The scheduling policy proposed in the paper involves optimizing system capacity, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also involves the use of simulation and optimization techniques, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Information Theory (cs.IT).
